</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A250A2FF3486F1DA3FC5F1FE827E81" lastPageId="227" lastPageNumber="228" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3F070329FF3486F1DA3FC5F1FE827E81" blockId="226.[810,1451,2009,2070]" lastBlockId="227.[136,778,173,1458]" lastPageId="227" lastPageNumber="228" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3486F0DA3FC5F1FC417AC6" bold="true" box="[810,934,2009,2035]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anus separated from anal-fin origin, closer to pelvic-fin bases; periproct teardrop-shaped, moderately developed. Small dermal window of light organ between pelvic-fin bases. Infraorbital ridge not connected with preopercular ridge, separated by distinct gap. Second spinous ray of first dorsal fin finely serrated along its leading edge. Pelvic fin inserted below or anterior to pectoral-fin base. Mouth moderately large, usually subterminal. Chin barbel well developed. Teeth small, in broad bands in both jaws; premaxillary band ending anterior to posterior edge of maxillary process. Tip and lateral angles of snout lacking prominent scutes in most species. Suborbital region almost vertical, without coarsely modified scales. Head fully scaled, except for narrow naked area above upper lip. Body scales not deciduous, closely adhered to body surfaces; scale spinules needle-like, densely scattered over exposed portion or tightly packed subparallel to convergent rows; buttresses of spinules rudimentary; reticulate structure developed on posterior parts of unexposed portion. Grooved lateral line present. Cephalic sensory pores present or absent. Branchiostegal rays 7. Body dark to swarthy, lacking silvery reflection when fresh. [Modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1D829C15FFD947EA4" author="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T." box="[316,627,887,914]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="27 - 95" refId="ref298977" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (1992) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) of the Nazca and Sala y Gomez Ridges, southeastern Pacific. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 48, 27 - 95." type="journal article" year="1992">Sazonov &amp; Iwamoto(1992)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1DBB1C150FEBC7E81" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Graham, K. J." pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="407 - 509" refId="ref288409" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Graham, K. J. (2001) Grenadiers (families Bathygadidae and Macrouridae, Gadiformes, Pisces) of New South Wales, Australia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 52, 407 - 509." type="journal article" year="2001">Iwamoto &amp; Graham (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A250A2FF3586F1D9A8C193FDB47884" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3F070329FF3586F1D9A8C193FDB47884" blockId="227.[136,778,173,1458]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1D9A8C193FED67EE0" bold="true" box="[189,305,955,981]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3586F1D828C194FE347EE0" authorityName="Iwamoto" authorityYear="1974" box="[317,467,956,981]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Kuronezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1D828C194FE347EE0" box="[317,467,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">Kuronezumia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally established as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3586F1D849C1F6FE597EC2" authorityName="Jordan in Jordan &amp; Starks" authorityYear="1904" box="[348,446,990,1015]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1D849C1F6FE597EC2" box="[348,446,990,1015]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">Nezumia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FF3586F1D8DEC1F5FDF17EC2" box="[459,534,989,1015]" name="Jordan" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">Jordan</collectingCountry>
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1DB37C1F6FDDF7EC2" box="[546,568,990,1015]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1DB51C1F5FF24792C" author="Jordan, D. S. &amp; Starks, E. C." pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="577 - 630" refId="ref290133" refString="Jordan, D. S. &amp; Starks, E. C. (1904) List of fishes dredged by the steamer Albatross off the coast of Japan in the summer of 1900, with descriptions of new species and a review of the Japanese Macrouridae. Bulletin of the U. S. Fish Commission, 22, 577 - 630, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1904">
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FF3586F1DB51C1F5FD687EC2" box="[580,655,989,1015]" name="Jordan" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">Jordan</collectingCountry>
&amp; Starks, 1904
</bibRefCitation>
, but 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1D9EDC1D7FDD6792C" author="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T." box="[248,561,1023,1050]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="27 - 95" refId="ref298977" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (1992) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) of the Nazca and Sala y Gomez Ridges, southeastern Pacific. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 48, 27 - 95." type="journal article" year="1992">Sazonov &amp; Iwamoto (1992)</bibRefCitation>
elevated this taxon to full generic rank. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1D87AC609FD79790E" author="Shcherbachev, Y. N. &amp; Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T." box="[367,670,1057,1083]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="97 - 108" refId="ref299815" refString="Shcherbachev, Y. N., Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (1992) Synopsis of the grenadier genus Kuronezumia (Pisces: Gadiformes: Macrouridae), with description of a new species. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 48, 97 - 108." type="journal article" year="1992">
Shcherbachev 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1DB06C60AFDAB790E" box="[531,588,1057,1083]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">et al.</emphasis>
(1992)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a synopsis for all the then-known species (seven species), viz., 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3586F1D9D6C64EFE11794A" authority="Iwamoto, 1974" authorityName="Iwamoto" authorityYear="1974" box="[195,502,1125,1152]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bubonis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1D9D6C64EFEA7794A" box="[195,320,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">K. bubonis</emphasis>
Iwamoto, 1974
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFF3586F1DB1DC64DFDDD794A" box="[520,570,1125,1151]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">type</typeStatus>
species); 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3586F1DBA4C64EFE4E7997" authority="(Gilbert &amp; Hubbs, 1916)" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Kuronezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dara">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3586F1DBA4C64EFCED794A" box="[689,778,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="227" pageNumber="228">K. dara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3586F1D985C6AFFE467997" author="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Hubbs, C. L." box="[144,417,1159,1186]" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" pagination="135 - 214" refId="ref285931" refString="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Hubbs, C. L. (1916) Report on the Japanese macrourid fishes collected by the United States fisheries steamer &quot; Albatross &quot; in 1906, with a synopsis of the genera. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 51, 135 - 214, pls. 8 - 11. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.51 - 2149.135" type="journal article" year="1916">Gilbert &amp; Hubbs, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3586F1D8ADC6A0FD067997" authority="(Barnard, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[440,737,1159,1186]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Kuronezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="227" pageNumber="228" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leonis">
